node.title: Truck carrying tiny home crashes in West Auckland
node.description: The truck collided with another vehicle, police say.
node.content:
["", "
\nPhoto: RNZ / Marika Khabazi\n
", "West Auckland drivers are facing delays after a truck carrying a tiny home crashed on Great North Road.", "Police say the truck collided with another vehicle, partially blocking the road near the intersection with Archibald Road.", "A witness said the truck had just picked up the tiny home from a lot across the street.", "Police were at the scene with tow trucks to move the damaged truck, police said.", "One person was taken to hospital with moderate injuries.", "Diversions were in place for traffic."]
